.TH CUSTODIA-ADMIN 1 "@DATE@" "Custodia @VERSION@" "Custodia Manual"
.SH NAME
custodia-admin \- administer a Custodia vault and certificate workflow
.SH SYNOPSIS
.SY custodia-admin
.OP --server-url URL
.OP --cert FILE
.OP --key FILE
.OP --ca FILE
.I command
.RI [ arguments ...]
.YS
.SY custodia-admin
.B version
.YS
.SY custodia-admin
.B --version
.YS
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B custodia-admin
is the operator CLI for Custodia. It talks to the vault API over mTLS,
performs metadata-only administration, exports and verifies audit material,
and orchestrates client certificate workflows.
.PP
On standard local installs, first-run admin reads such as
.B status read
and
.B diagnostics read
derive the server URL and admin mTLS paths from
.I /etc/custodia/custodia-server.yaml.
When the admin certificate and key live under
.I /etc/custodia,
run the command as the restricted
.B custodia
service user, for example:
.PP
.EX
sudo -u custodia custodia-admin status read
.EE
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B version
Print local build metadata and exit without contacting the server.
.TP
.B version server
Print server build metadata from
.BR /v1/version .
.TP
.B client create --client-id ID --mtls-subject SUBJECT
Register client metadata in the vault.
.TP
.B ca bootstrap-local --out-dir DIR --admin-client-id ID --server-name NAME
Generate Lite first-run CA material. Do not pass localhost as the server name;
use the DNS name clients and browsers will actually use. IP addresses are supported,
but DNS is strongly recommended for operational stability.
.TP
.B client enrollment create [--config FILE] [--ttl DURATION]
Create a short-lived, one-shot enrollment token for remote client onboarding. The command reads the configured server URL from the server YAML and prints the token and server URL for transfer to the client host.
.TP
.B client sign-csr --client-id ID --csr-file FILE --certificate-out FILE --signer-url URL
Register client metadata, submit a client-generated CSR to
.BR custodia-signer (1),
and write the signed client certificate. This manual/offline flow keeps the client mTLS private key on the client host.
.TP
.B client csr --client-id ID --private-key-out FILE --csr-out FILE
Generate a local client mTLS private key and CSR. Prefer
.BR custodia-client " mtls generate-csr"
for remote client workstations.
.TP
.B client issue --client-id ID --out-dir DIR --signer-url URL
Register client metadata, generate local mTLS key/CSR, submit the CSR to
.BR custodia-signer (1),
extract the certificate, and create a local certificate bundle. This is a
convenience path for all-in-one Lite/lab hosts.
.TP
.B certificate sign --client-id ID --csr-file FILE
Submit a CSR to the signing service.
.TP
.B certificate extract --input FILE --certificate-out FILE
Extract a certificate PEM from signer JSON output.
.TP
.B certificate bundle --certificate FILE --private-key FILE --ca FILE --out FILE
Create a local ZIP bundle containing client mTLS material.
.TP
.B audit export
Export bounded audit metadata.
.TP
.B audit verify-export
Verify exported audit body/digest/count artifacts.
.TP
.B secret versions --key KEY [--namespace NS] [--limit N]
List metadata for versions of the selected namespace/key secret. The command does
not print ciphertext or recipient envelopes.
.TP
.B access list --key KEY [--namespace NS] [--limit N]
List active access metadata for the selected namespace/key secret.
.TP
.B access grant-request --key KEY [--namespace NS] --client-id ID --permissions read[,write,share]
Create a pending access grant request for a target client. The selected secret is
resolved by namespace/key; generated server ids are not part of normal operator
input.
.TP
.B access activate --key KEY [--namespace NS] --client-id ID --envelope-file FILE
Activate a pending grant using the opaque client-generated envelope stored in
FILE.
.TP
.B access revoke --key KEY [--namespace NS] --client-id ID
Revoke future server-side access for the selected client and namespace/key secret.
.TP
.B production check
Run production configuration checks from an environment file.
.TP
.B web totp configure [--config FILE] [--issuer NAME] [--account NAME]
Generate first-run Web MFA material, append it to the server YAML config, print
the TOTP secret and provisioning URI, and print a terminal QR code when
.B qrencode
is available.
.TP
.B doctor [--server-config FILE] [--signer-config FILE] [--systemd] [--network]
Run read-only installation diagnostics. The default mode is offline and checks
configuration parsing, profile/backend coherence, required files, key modes and
runtime directories. Optional flags add systemd unit checks and TCP listener
reachability checks.
.SH GLOBAL OPTIONS
.TP
.BI --server-url " URL"
Custodia API base URL. For first-run admin reads, defaults to the local server YAML when omitted.
.TP
.BI --cert " FILE"
Admin mTLS client certificate. For first-run admin reads, defaults to the local server YAML signer client certificate when omitted.
.TP
.BI --key " FILE"
Admin mTLS private key. For first-run admin reads, defaults to the local server YAML signer client key when omitted.
.TP
.BI --ca " FILE"
Custodia CA certificate. For first-run admin reads, defaults to the local server YAML signer client CA when omitted.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SERVER_URL
Default Custodia API URL.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_CLIENT_CERT_FILE
Default admin mTLS certificate path.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_CLIENT_KEY_FILE
Default admin mTLS private key path.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SERVER_CA_FILE
Default server CA certificate path.
.TP
.B CUSTODIA_SIGNER_URL
Default signer URL for client certificate issue workflows.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/admin.crt
Default local admin mTLS certificate.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/admin.key
Default local admin mTLS private key. Keep readable only by root/custodia.
.TP
.I /etc/custodia/ca.crt
Default Custodia CA certificate.
.TP
.I /var/log/custodia/
Default server and signer log directory for packaged installs.
.SH SECURITY NOTES
.B custodia-admin
must not handle secret plaintext, DEKs, recipient envelopes, or application
private encryption keys. It is an administrative metadata and certificate
workflow tool.
.PP
Prefer running commands that read
.I /etc/custodia/admin.key
as the
.B custodia
service user instead of unrestricted root.
.SH EXAMPLES
Create a remote-client enrollment token:
.PP
.EX
sudo -u custodia custodia-admin client enrollment create --ttl 15m
.EE

Configure first-run Web TOTP material in the server YAML:
.PP
.EX
sudo custodia-admin web totp configure --account admin
.EE
.SH VERSION
Custodia version: @VERSION@
.br
Build commit: @COMMIT@
.br
Build date: @DATE@
.PP
Runtime version is available with:
.PP
.EX
custodia-admin version
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Runtime or API failure.
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.IR docs/DOCTOR.md ,
.BR custodia-client (1),
.BR custodia-server (1),
.BR custodia-signer (1)
